<br>
I'd like to appologize to anyone that was offended or concerned by my use of the term &quot;merger.&quot;  I've spilled so many thousands of words on this topic so far I can't even count them anymore and perhaps I'm not thinking as carefully as I used to about each individual one.<br>
<br>
The Traders Union has ended as a guild.  Most of the founding members and officers have either joined, are in the process of joining, or are intending to apply to join Starspun.  This process has been slowed by negotiations, explanations, the holiday season, and quite a few hardware problems owing to the new release.  Overall, however, I doubt that even if we were all to join we would end up making up more than 20% of Starspun ever, and that's an extreme estimate.<br>
<br>
The former members of the Traders Union joining with Starspun are joining as regular members, up to and including our former guild leader and first officer (myself) and we have no immediate ambitions to seek higher position.  We are and will continue to be guided by the principles of Starspun as it was before, and as it continues to evolve.  If anything I've ever suggested sounded otherwise, I appoligize again.<br>
<br>
That much being said, there will be far more master tradesmen in Starspun now, as well as a few that were already there, so if you need to look for a tradesmen feel free to ask us.<br>
<br>
I have maintained my jewelry website at www.tradersjewelry.freeservers.com and I believe I will maintain the Traders Union as a non-guild trade organization, spanning guild lines and including independents.  At least for jewelry thus far, and perhaps for other trades if I find people to spearhead that.  Provided the officers of Starspun find no conflict in this.<br>
<br>
In service to all.<br>
<br>
